<section style="max-width: 50em">
        <h1>Shadows</h1>
        <p class="air"> The shadow classes are found inside the shadow.css <br>
         <hr> 
            CSS to help you give shadow and hover on boxes. 
        </p>
        <dl class="sq-dl sq-dl-divider">
            <dt>Classes</dt>
            <dd class="sq-shadow-lt sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-lt</strong> - This is displaying the light class shadow with hover effect.</dd> 
            <dd class="sq-shadow-lt:hover sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-lt:hover</strong> - This is the hover class, used on the example above.</dd>
            <dd class="sq-shadow-sm sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-sm</strong> - This is displaying the small shadow class.</dd>
            <dd class="sq-shadow-md sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-md</strong> - This is displaying the medium shadow class.</dd> 
            <dd class="sq-shadow-lg sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-lg</strong> - This is displaying the large shadow class.</dd>
            <dd class="sq-shadow-xl sq-margin-2"><strong>sq-shadow-xl</strong> - This is displaying the extra large shadow class.</dd>        
            <pre class="code">
                    <code>
&ltdiv class="sq-shadow-lt" &gt
    ...add content/text+++...
&lt/div&gt
                    </code>
                </pre>  
